    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Reopening: a proper solution to [issue 12531](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/12531) is going to mean that shutting down a channel potentially blocks for the duration of the connectivity poll, and it doesn't seem like a good idea to me to block application code (or the garbage collector, or... whatever else it happens to be that shuts down the channel) for two hundred milliseconds."
